Sentencas: A polarization model for a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) with a bi-layer electrolyte is developed and a set of explicit expressions for output current, maximum power and thickness ratio of bi-layer electrolyte are obtained.
Titulo: A polarization model for solid oxide fuel cells with a Bi-layer electrolyte

Sentencas: In the model, two dominating polarizations, activation polarization and ohmic polarization, are considered and the concentration polarization is neglected.
Titulo: A polarization model for solid oxide fuel cells with a Bi-layer electrolyte

Sentencas: The activation polarization at the electrodes is described by the Butler-Volmer equation.
Titulo: A polarization model for solid oxide fuel cells with a Bi-layer electrolyte

Sentencas: The ohmic polarization is represented by the charge transport equation, and this equation is solved with the assumption of constant ionic conductivity.
Titulo: A polarization model for solid oxide fuel cells with a Bi-layer electrolyte

Sentencas: To close the model equations, a supplemental relation is introduced by the energy conservation analysis.
Titulo: A polarization model for solid oxide fuel cells with a Bi-layer electrolyte

Sentencas: The modeling results compare well with the experimental data.
Titulo: A polarization model for solid oxide fuel cells with a Bi-layer electrolyte

Sentencas: The model is further used to study the effect of cathode exchange current density on the working characteristics of a solid oxide fuel cell with a bi-layer electrolyte.
Titulo: A polarization model for solid oxide fuel cells with a Bi-layer electrolyte
